  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean ears?",
  "response": "Cleaning your ears should be done carefully to avoid damaging sensitive structures like the eardrum or ear canal. Here are some safe methods:\n\n1. **Natural Cleaning:** Your ears usually clean themselves. The skin in your ears grows outward, encouraging earwax to naturally exit the ear canal.\n\n2. **Warm Water:** During a shower, let a little warm water run into your ear, then tilt your head to allow it to flow out and dry your ear with a towel.\n\n3. **Ear Drops:** Over-the-counter ear drops can help soften earwax, making it easier for your ear to expel it naturally. Follow the instructions on the packaging.\n\n4. **Hydrogen Peroxide:** Mix equal parts of hydrogen peroxide and water, place a few drops into the ear, and let it sit for a few minutes before tilting your head to drain it out and dry your ear gently.\n\n5. **Olive Oil:** A few drops of warm (not hot) olive oil in the ear can help soften the earwax. After a few minutes, tilt your head to let it flow out and clean the outer ear gently.\n\n**Avoid:**\n- Cotton swabs: These can push wax deeper into the ear canal or cause injury.\n- Sharp objects: Never use hairpins, matchsticks, or similar items.\n- Ear candles: These are not recommended due to the risk of burns and lack of evidence for effectiveness.\n\n**Visit a Doctor:**\nIf you suspect a blockage, experience pain, or have difficulty hearing, it's best to consult a healthcare professional. They can safely remove earwax build-up.",
